      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BONNIE BLITZ (7) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when third (24.23) over 425m at this track. Solid formlines coming through her last run. One of the contenders. SCOTT EPHRAIM (1) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at his last four runs. Last time finished 2nd over 450m at Shepparton beaten half a length (25.54) behind Paw Oltron in a Mix 6/7 on March 2. Leading chance. GREYSYND CLYDE (4) had a low draw last time over 450m at Shepparton but was in traffic and fell. No luck latest and gets chance to atone. PENNY'S LEGACY (2) is worth a look despite no experience at this circuit.",
